The '''Sumers Lodge''' in [[Glenwood Springs, Colorado]] is a rustic log house built in 1935. The house was built for New York financier [[George Sumers]].  It was designed by Chilson Aldrich, and some of its furnishings were designed and made by [[Thomas C. Molesworth]].<ref name="cohistso1">{{cite web|title=Garfield County|url=http://www.coloradohistory-oahp.org/programareas/register/1503/cty/gf.htm|work=Listings by County|publisher=Colorado Historical Society|accessdate=18 August 2010}}</ref><ref name="cowboyhighstyle1">{{cite book|last=Flood|first=Elizabeth Clair|title=Cowboy High Style: Thomas Molesworth to the New West|year=1992|publisher=Gibbs Smith|isbn=0-87905-872-X|page=30|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=R3vb-BlbVYkC&lpg=PP1&ots=btml_7bETV&dq=%22Thomas%20C.%20Molesworth%22&pg=PA14#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>

The Sumers Lodge is a large two story rectangular log structure with a projecting sun porch on the entrance side.<ref name="corustic1">{{cite web|title=Sumers Lodge|url=http://www.coloradohistory-oahp.org/publications/pubs/1642.pdf|work=Directory of Rustic Style Architecture in the State Register|publisher=Colorado Historical Society|accessdate=18 August 2010|year=2007}}</ref>

